tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE ElectricVehiclesEnergyConsumption (
    vehicle_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_model VARCHAR(255),
    energy_consumed DECIMAL,
    charging_stations_used INT,
    city VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE ChargingHistory (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT NOT NULL,
    station_id INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP,
    energy_consumed DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE ElectricVehiclesEnergyConsumption (
    vehicle_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    brand VARCHAR(50),
    model VARCHAR(50),
    battery_capacity FLOAT,
    charging_station_id INT
);

CREATE TABLE ChargingStations (
    station_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_name VARCHAR(50),
    city VARCHAR(50),
    country VARCHAR(50),
    total_chargers INT
);

CREATE TABLE ChargingLogs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    station_id INT,
    charging_start DATETIME,
    charging_end DATETIME,
    energy_consumed FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES ElectricVehiclesEnergyConsumption(vehicle_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (station_id) REFERENCES ChargingStations(station_id)
);

CREATE TABLE charging_history (
    history_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    station_id INT,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);
